
# Data Requirements

## Input Dataset

This project uses historical daily stock price data for multiple assets across different sectors.

Current assets used:

* Reliance
* Power Grid
* NTPC
* HDFC Bank
* ICICI Bank
* Sun Pharma
* ITC

These are grouped into sector clusters for Correlation Matrix Modeling (CCM).

---

## Required CSV Format

Each CSV file must contain at least:

### 1. Date Column

Used for time-series indexing.

Example:

```text id="f2k7as"
Date
```

---

### 2. Price Column

Used for return calculation.

The code currently detects columns containing:

```text id="2zjlwm"
EQN
```

so the adjusted closing price / closing price column should contain this naming pattern.

Example:

```text id="mqxwju"
EQN Price
```

or

```text id="gf9v7d"
EQN
```

---

## Example CSV Structure

```text id="fh0vll"
Date,EQN
2023-01-01,2450.50
2023-01-02,2471.30
2023-01-03,2438.10
...
```

---

## Data Preprocessing

The model automatically performs:

* column name cleaning
* date conversion using pandas datetime
* date indexing
* log return calculation

using:

$$
r_t = \ln\left(\frac{P_t}{P_{t-1}}\right)
$$

r_t = \ln\left(\frac{P_t}{P_{t-1}}\right)

---

## Train-Test Split

The dataset is divided into:

* 70% Training Data
* 30% Testing Data

Where:

### Training Data is used for:

* ARIMA fitting
* GARCH volatility forecasting
* Correlation Matrix construction
* Robust Optimization

### Testing Data is used for:

* out-of-sample validation
* portfolio performance measurement
* Sharpe ratio evaluation

---

## Important Notes

* Missing values should be removed before use
* Data should be aligned across all assets
* Same date frequency should be maintained
* Prefer daily adjusted closing prices for better consistency

---

## Future Improvement

The model can be further improved by adding:

* benchmark index data (like NIFTY 50)
* sector index returns
* macroeconomic factors
* factor model inputs for Black-Litterman implementation

This will improve expected return estimation significantly.
